article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- — Tom Mark's 16 points helped CSU Bakersfield defeat Cal Poly 65-53 on Saturday night. Mark added seven rebounds and three steals for the Roadrunners (7-11, 2-5 Big West Conference). Kaleb Higgins scored 14 points, shooting 5 of 12 from the field and 4 for 4 from the foul line. Modestas Kancleris finished 4 of 11 from the field to finish with nine points. The Mustangs (4-15, 0-7) were led by Quentin Jones, who posted 16 points. Kobe Sanders added 10 points for Cal Poly. Paul Bizimana also recorded nine points, six rebounds and two steals. The loss is the seventh in a row for the Mustangs. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
